1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,333
welcome back

2
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:04,933
today we are going to harness the power of the core

3
00:00:05,033 --> 00:00:08,500
and the first thing we are going to need is some tiberium

4
00:00:08,666 --> 00:00:10,933
this can be obtained on Ross's moon

5
00:00:10,933 --> 00:00:13,400
which requires a tier 5 rocket

6
00:00:14,066 --> 00:00:15,200
we quickly craft it

7
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,333
and then launch to our new adventure

8
00:00:17,666 --> 00:00:20,066
once we arrive at the new destination

9
00:00:20,066 --> 00:00:23,633
the first thing we notice is how fast the day passes here

10
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:26,233
and after some prospecting

11
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:28,500
we quickly find some Tiberium

12
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:30,433
after collecting some of it

13
00:00:30,433 --> 00:00:33,200
we quickly craft the new fuel rods

14
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:36,133
then after doing a backup

15
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:39,833
we try to see how it behaves inside a nuclear reactor

16
00:00:40,266 --> 00:00:44,433
and it looks like our current system can barely handle those rods

17
00:00:44,866 --> 00:00:46,200
the real issue is that

18
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:49,266
due to the huge heat produced by such fuel

19
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:51,533
if our coolant system were to fail

20
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:53,900
the reactor will instantly evaporate

21
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:57,800
to contain the mess in case of explosion

22
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,200
we can add some reactor platings

23
00:01:01,866 --> 00:01:04,933
or by adding enough heat capacity plates

24
00:01:04,933 --> 00:01:07,066
we can make our reactor able to tank 

25
00:01:07,066 --> 00:01:10,700
up to four seconds of exposure to such powerful fuel

26
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:15,700
and that should be enough time for our Thermal Protection to trigger

27
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:17,666
and thus

28
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:19,666
we came up with this design

29
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:21,333
where there are six rods

30
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:24,500
each with four dedicated coolant cells

31
00:01:25,266 --> 00:01:28,333
the power output is 600 thousand EU per tick

32
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:30,300
doubling what we had before

33
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:33,000
however that didn't last long

34
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:33,900
it looks like

35
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:36,466
some heat managed to escape to the reactor hull

36
00:01:36,466 --> 00:01:38,600
and triggered our Thermal Protection

37
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:42,333
and the culprit seems to be our underpaid vacuum freezer

38
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:45,600
which is still working only on MV wage

39
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:48,633
so we gave it a rise to EV

40
00:01:49,266 --> 00:01:52,666
however our power balance is now negative again

41
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:55,700
so we must find a more powerful design

42
00:01:57,533 --> 00:01:59,500
and after some crafting

43
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:02,733
we can finally use the 40 rods famous one

44
00:02:03,233 --> 00:02:06,266
this configuration is extremely dangerous

45
00:02:06,266 --> 00:02:08,300
because there is nothing saving our base

46
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:11,733
if the reactor were to run with a too low amount of coolant

47
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,800
to do a quick test

48
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,933
we are going to run the reactor for a second

49
00:02:15,933 --> 00:02:18,333
with the help of a button and a screwdriver

50
00:02:19,066 --> 00:02:19,533
and here

51
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:23,933
we can see that our coolants took quite the hit from just that small run

52
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,433
we can do a second push

53
00:02:26,433 --> 00:02:29,100
and see that we are already over half of the coolant

54
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:31,466
but the power output is really high

55
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:35,900
now we shall try to find a way of automating that thing

56
00:02:36,233 --> 00:02:36,933
to do so

57
00:02:36,933 --> 00:02:39,700
we need three buttons and lamps

58
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:42,033
the first one will run the reactor

59
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:45,100
the second one will extract the coolant

60
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:50,733
and it appears that this is going to need more than a push to finish its job

61
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:53,400
once the exhaust is out

62
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:57,800
we can use the third button to insert new fresh coolant cells

63
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:02,100
managing to automate cells that get burned up so fast

64
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:04,266
is going to be too risky and hard

65
00:03:04,266 --> 00:03:07,600
so we shall instead switch to some bigger ones

66
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:11,400
the issue is that those require fluxed electrum

67
00:03:11,466 --> 00:03:14,100
which has to be cooked in a ZPM

68
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,466
trinium coil DBF

69
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:19,933
and trinium coils require a ZPM assembler

70
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,433
since we already have all the requirements

71
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:25,800
we quickly rush the ZPM assembler

72
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:29,133
which we use to upgrade our volcanoes

73
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:29,900
thus

74
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:33,100
allowing for the crafting of the best coolant cells

75
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:35,300
now that we have better coolant

76
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:38,333
we can start using levers instead of buttons

77
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:40,600
we carefully turn on the reactor

78
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,000
and watch as it works

79
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:44,500
and when we turn it off

80
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,033
some fire happens

81
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:47,000
fear not

82
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:52,000
that was just our thin cable that couldn't handle the power output of our reactor

83
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:55,933
we shall switch to the only cable capable of handling so many amps

84
00:03:55,933 --> 00:03:58,233
superconductor 16x

85
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:00,600
once the new cable is in place

86
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,466
we can go back to our tests

87
00:04:02,466 --> 00:04:03,800
and move to stage 2

88
00:04:03,866 --> 00:04:05,933
extracting the used coolant

89
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:08,500
finally in the third stage

90
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:10,266
we insert new fresh coolant

91
00:04:10,266 --> 00:04:13,033
and we are ready for another iteration of the loop

92
00:04:13,866 --> 00:04:14,400
however 

93
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,900
that is not how we are going to do it

94
00:04:17,066 --> 00:04:20,200
we want it to be automatically managed by a timer

95
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:24,733
but we can't be careless and just directly connect it

96
00:04:25,466 --> 00:04:27,833
we will want to have some extra sensors

97
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:31,866
namely something that stops the thing if we run out of coolant

98
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:33,933
after some fiddling

99
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:36,433
we set up a system that will output a signal

100
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:39,000
if we have less than a change of cells

101
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:41,233
while at it

102
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:44,733
we also add a lever to manually shout down the reactor

103
00:04:44,933 --> 00:04:46,700
then we connect everything up

104
00:04:47,466 --> 00:04:50,700
and it was finally time to let that thing run on its own

105
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:54,866
since one whole iteration takes 7 seconds

106
00:04:54,866 --> 00:04:57,533
we can speed it up by seven times

107
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:08,333
and now there are two main issues

108
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,266
the first one

109
00:05:09,266 --> 00:05:12,233
is that we are not receiving the power output

110
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:16,233
which turned out to be a limitation of the plug of our battery

111
00:05:17,266 --> 00:05:19,766
this setup is making 150 amps

112
00:05:19,766 --> 00:05:22,433
and we could only absorb spikes of 80

113
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:24,633
the second issue is that

114
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:29,866
this setup is not going to produce our 150 amps LuV constantly

115
00:05:29,866 --> 00:05:32,033
but only 1/4 of the time

116
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:36,100
now exactly like a 4 strokes engine

117
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,933
that is okay if we have a light load with some inertia

118
00:05:38,933 --> 00:05:41,133
but not when we need a lot of power

119
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,466
so to make a good nuclear engine

120
00:05:44,466 --> 00:05:49,833
we are going to need three more cylinders filled with cylinders of cylinders of enriched naquadah

121
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:52,800
that required a lot of tiberium

122
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,033
and here came the realization

123
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:58,866
cooking all the tungsten steel for those cylinders

124
00:05:58,866 --> 00:06:01,200
is going to take quite some time

125
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:02,633
too much time

126
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:05,733
to do that in a reasonable amount of time

127
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:07,866
we shall have a bigger blast furnace

128
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:12,133
that thing is going to cook our tungsten steel twice as fast

129
00:06:12,133 --> 00:06:14,733
but it is also making way more pollution

130
00:06:15,733 --> 00:06:16,000
also

131
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,833
we are now using more power

132
00:06:17,833 --> 00:06:21,333
than what our single four strokes reactor can make

133
00:06:21,933 --> 00:06:23,433
and after some time

134
00:06:23,433 --> 00:06:26,666
we finally managed to finish our inline 4 engine

135
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:31,300
now let's see in the details how that thing works

136
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:35,433
every reactor has the same setup of the one we had before

137
00:06:36,533 --> 00:06:36,966
however

138
00:06:36,966 --> 00:06:39,066
we changed the working conditions

139
00:06:39,066 --> 00:06:42,533
and the four reactors have a 90 degrees phase offset

140
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,466
the new condition is that

141
00:06:45,466 --> 00:06:47,933
instead of just checking the coolant level

142
00:06:47,933 --> 00:06:50,433
we have a red wire that will allow for running

143
00:06:51,866 --> 00:06:54,333
that red wire is the output of an and gate

144
00:06:54,333 --> 00:06:57,400
of a lever, our coolant level and our battery level

145
00:06:58,233 --> 00:06:59,600
for both the levels

146
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,733
we have an RS latch

147
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,900
that will allow for smoother working

148
00:07:03,433 --> 00:07:05,300
and we wait up to 30 seconds

149
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,233
before reenabling the reactors

150
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:09,000
if we run low on coolant

151
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:13,400
and since the coolant is swapped even if the reactor doesn't run

152
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,200
we can filter the unused cells

153
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:17,433
to not go through the vacuum freezer

154
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:21,800
that's how the setup works with a 7x speed up

155
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:33,300
and while that thing can keep our batteries well charged up

156
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,066
we can do even better

157
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:38,633
we can do so by using a more optimal fuel layout

158
00:07:39,266 --> 00:07:40,900
in this configuration

159
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:44,933
each rod has exactly three nearby rods and one coolant cell

160
00:07:44,933 --> 00:07:47,866
that way the fuel is pushed to the maximum

161
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:52,633
also every coolant cells has exactly one rod to cool

162
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:55,500
making it last the longest time possible

163
00:07:55,733 --> 00:07:59,700
that will also lead to cells taking all the exact same damage

164
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:04,933
making it possible to easily filter them out of the reactor when they reach critical damage

165
00:08:05,466 --> 00:08:06,233
finally

166
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:09,233
we can fill the reactor with enough heat capacity plates

167
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:12,400
to make it able to withstand the loss of one cell

168
00:08:13,266 --> 00:08:17,700
meaning that we can try to automate the cell swap while the reactor runs

169
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,500
and for more ease

170
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:24,200
we must ensure all the cells are at a different damage level

171
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:28,266
so that only one has to be replaced or can fail every reactor tick

172
00:08:28,866 --> 00:08:29,700
and it was then

173
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:33,500
that I was unsure if it was an error or not following errors advice

174
00:08:34,266 --> 00:08:34,733
anyways

175
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:37,733
this setup seems to make quite enough power

176
00:08:39,433 --> 00:08:40,800
and to finish off

177
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:43,100
we add a condition that will turn on the reactors

178
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:46,500
only when our battery reaches a quarter of charge

179
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:49,733
and that is quite some toggling

180
00:08:50,466 --> 00:08:54,466
but with such a setup there is no need for latches

181
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:56,133
anyways

182
00:08:56,133 --> 00:09:00,900
I think we have fixed the power issues for at least one episode

183
00:09:01,033 --> 00:09:02,800
see you next time

184
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:03,533
bye bye

185
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,333
欢迎回来！

186
00:00:01,533 --> 00:00:04,933
今天我们要利用"核心"发电

187
00:00:05,033 --> 00:00:08,500
首先需要的是一些泰伯利亚矿

188
00:00:08,666 --> 00:00:10,933
可以在罗斯的卫星上挖掘

189
00:00:10,933 --> 00:00:13,400
这要 T5 火箭

190
00:00:14,066 --> 00:00:15,200
我们快速制作它

191
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:17,333
然后开始新的冒险

192
00:00:17,666 --> 00:00:20,066
一旦我们到达新的目的地

193
00:00:20,066 --> 00:00:23,633
可以注意到这里一天的时间飞逝

194
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:26,233
经过一番勘探

195
00:00:26,233 --> 00:00:28,500
我们很快找到了一些泰伯利亚矿

196
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:30,433
收集了一些后

197
00:00:30,433 --> 00:00:33,200
迅速做点新燃料棒

198
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:36,133
在进行备份后

199
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:39,833
我们尝试观察它在核反应堆中的行为

200
00:00:40,266 --> 00:00:44,433
看起来我们现有的系统几乎无法处理这些燃料棒

201
00:00:44,866 --> 00:00:46,200
真正的问题是

202
00:00:46,200 --> 00:00:49,266
由于此燃料棒带来的巨量热量

203
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:51,533
如果冷却系统失灵

204
00:00:51,533 --> 00:00:53,900
反应堆会瞬间被蒸发

205
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:57,800
以防发生爆炸

206
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:00,200
我们可以添加一些反应堆板

207
00:01:01,866 --> 00:01:04,933
或者通过添加足够的热容量板

208
00:01:04,933 --> 00:01:07,066
让我们的反应堆

209
00:01:07,066 --> 00:01:10,700
在如此强大的燃料下承受长达 4 秒钟

210
00:01:11,900 --> 00:01:15,700
4 秒足够启动热防护系统了

211
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:17,666
因此

212
00:01:17,666 --> 00:01:19,666
我们得到这个设计

213
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:21,333
总共有六个燃料棒

214
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:24,500
每个燃料棒都有四个专用的冷却单元

215
00:01:25,266 --> 00:01:28,333
输出功率高达 600 kEU/t

216
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:30,300
比以前多了一倍

217
00:01:30,600 --> 00:01:33,000
然而这并没有持续多久

218
00:01:33,233 --> 00:01:33,900
似乎

219
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:36,466
一些热量设法逃逸到反应堆外壳

220
00:01:36,466 --> 00:01:38,600
触发了我们的热防护系统

221
00:01:39,033 --> 00:01:42,333
罪魁祸首似乎是我们低能效的冰箱

222
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:45,600
它仍然只以 MV 电压工作

223
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:48,633
所以我们将其升至 EV

224
00:01:49,266 --> 00:01:52,666
然而现在的电力收支又转成赤字

225
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:55,700
所以我们必须找到更强大的设计

226
00:01:57,533 --> 00:01:59,500
经过一番精心制作

227
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:02,733
也是用上了最出名的 40 燃料棒设计

228
00:02:03,233 --> 00:02:06,266
这种配置极其危险

229
00:02:06,266 --> 00:02:08,300
如果反应堆的冷却单元太少

230
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:11,733
我们的基地就等待毁灭吧

231
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:13,800
做一个快速测试

232
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,933
在按钮和螺丝刀的帮助下

233
00:02:15,933 --> 00:02:18,333
我们让反应堆运行一秒

234
00:02:19,533 --> 00:02:23,933
我们可以看到冷却单元受到了不小的冲击

235
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:26,433
再按一次

236
00:02:26,433 --> 00:02:29,100
已经有一半的冷却单元出现问题

237
00:02:29,100 --> 00:02:31,466
但输出功率真的很高

238
00:02:32,433 --> 00:02:35,900
现在我们尝试找到一种自动化的方法

239
00:02:36,233 --> 00:02:36,933
为此

240
00:02:36,933 --> 00:02:39,700
我们需要三个按钮和灯

241
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:42,033
第一个将运行反应堆

242
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:45,100
第二个会抽出冷却单元

243
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:50,733
看来想完成工作不仅仅只是按一次那么简单

244
00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:53,400
一旦抽取

245
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:57,800
我们用第三个按钮插入新的冷却单元

246
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:02,100
想给损毁如此快的单元自动化

247
00:03:02,100 --> 00:03:04,266
实在是太冒险了

248
00:03:04,266 --> 00:03:07,600
所以我们应该换一些容量大的

249
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:11,400
问题是那些需要通流琥珀金

250
00:03:11,466 --> 00:03:13,366
它必须在 ZPM 电压

251
00:03:13,366 --> 00:03:15,466
使用三元金属线圈的高炉烧制

252
00:03:16,233 --> 00:03:19,933
而三元金属线圈需要 ZPM 组装机

253
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,433
既然已经有了需求

254
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:25,800
我们就快速做出 ZPM 组装机

255
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:29,133
用它来升级炽焰高炉

256
00:03:29,533 --> 00:03:29,900
由此

257
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:33,100
制作出最好的冷却单元

258
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:35,300
有了它们

259
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:38,333
可以将拉杆换掉按钮了

260
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:40,600
我们小心地打开反应堆

261
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:42,000
看着它工作

262
00:03:42,433 --> 00:03:44,500
当我们关掉它时

263
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,033
有些火焰冒了出来

264
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:47,000
不要害怕

265
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:52,000
这是线缆最大荷载太低导致的

266
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:55,933
我们切换至唯一能胜任这个工作的线缆

267
00:03:55,933 --> 00:03:58,233
LuV 超导线缆 16x

268
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:00,600
一旦新电缆到位

269
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,366
我们回到测试

270
00:04:02,366 --> 00:04:03,866
进入第二阶段

271
00:04:03,866 --> 00:04:05,933
抽取用过的冷却单元

272
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:08,500
最后是第三阶段

273
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:10,266
插入新的冷却单元

274
00:04:10,266 --> 00:04:13,033
这样就能进行下一个循环了

275
00:04:13,866 --> 00:04:14,400
然而 

276
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,900
这不是我们想要达成的效果

277
00:04:17,066 --> 00:04:20,200
我们想用计时器自动控制

278
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:24,733
不要粗心地直接把计时器接入电路

279
00:04:25,466 --> 00:04:27,833
我们需要一些额外的传感器

280
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:31,866
在冷却单元用尽后自动停止

281
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:33,933
经过一番摆弄

282
00:04:33,933 --> 00:04:36,433
我们设置了一套系统

283
00:04:36,433 --> 00:04:39,000
只要缺少了冷却单元就会输出信号

284
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:41,233
同时

285
00:04:41,233 --> 00:04:44,733
还增加了一个拉杆来手动控制

286
00:04:44,933 --> 00:04:46,700
然后把一切都连接起来

287
00:04:47,466 --> 00:04:50,700
是时候让它自己运行了

288
00:04:51,700 --> 00:04:54,866
因为整个迭代需要 7 秒

289
00:04:54,866 --> 00:04:57,533
所以我们加速 7 倍

290
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:08,333
现在有两个主要问题

291
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,266
第一

292
00:05:09,266 --> 00:05:12,233
我们没有收到能量输出

293
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:16,233
这是能源仓的问题

294
00:05:17,266 --> 00:05:19,766
这套核电输出了 150A 的电流

295
00:05:19,766 --> 00:05:22,433
但电池只能接收 80A

296
00:05:23,333 --> 00:05:24,633
第二个问题是

297
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:29,866
它不会持续产生 150A LuV

298
00:05:29,866 --> 00:05:32,033
只有四分之一的时间在输出

299
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:36,100
就像一个四冲程引擎

300
00:05:36,100 --> 00:05:38,933
如果负载较轻并带有惯性的话，那也没问题

301
00:05:38,933 --> 00:05:41,133
但高负载时就力不从心

302
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,466
所以想造一个优质核电

303
00:05:44,466 --> 00:05:49,833
满载硅岩燃料的另外三台核电很必须

304
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:52,800
而这也需要大量的硅岩

305
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,033
然后我意识到

306
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:58,866
为这些单元烧完钨钢

307
00:05:58,866 --> 00:06:01,200
需要相当长的时间

308
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:02,633
难以忍受的长

309
00:06:03,233 --> 00:06:05,733
要在合理的时间内做到这一点

310
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:07,866
少不了巨高炉

311
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:12,133
那东西能以两倍的速度烧制钨钢

312
00:06:12,133 --> 00:06:14,733
但也有更多污染

313
00:06:15,733 --> 00:06:16,000
而且

314
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,833
我们现在的耗能

315
00:06:17,833 --> 00:06:21,333
比单个四冲程反应堆产生的还多

316
00:06:21,933 --> 00:06:23,433
一段时间后

317
00:06:23,433 --> 00:06:26,666
我们终于完成了“四联引擎”

318
00:06:27,533 --> 00:06:31,300
让我们详细看看它是如何工作的

319
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:35,433
每个反应堆都和之前的一样

320
00:06:36,533 --> 00:06:36,966
然而

321
00:06:36,966 --> 00:06:39,066
我们改变了工作条件

322
00:06:39,066 --> 00:06:42,533
而且四个反应堆各有90度的相位偏移

323
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,466
新的条件是

324
00:06:45,466 --> 00:06:47,933
不仅是检查冷却单元的损伤

325
00:06:47,933 --> 00:06:50,433
我们用一条红线控制反应堆启停

326
00:06:51,866 --> 00:06:54,333
那条红线是与门的输出

327
00:06:54,333 --> 00:06:57,400
结合了拉杆、冷却单元数量和电池电量

328
00:06:58,233 --> 00:06:59,600
对于后两个红石信号

329
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,733
我们用一个 RS 锁存器

330
00:07:00,733 --> 00:07:02,900
来使反应堆工作更顺畅

331
00:07:03,433 --> 00:07:05,300
如果冷却单元用完了

332
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,233
我们要等 30 秒

333
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:09,000
才会重启反应堆

334
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:13,400
因为即使反应堆不运行冷却单元也会被交换

335
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,200
我们过滤未使用的单元

336
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:17,433
不让它再进入冰箱

337
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:21,800
这就是产线 7 倍速工作的样子

338
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:33,300
虽说那东西能让电池饱餐一顿

339
00:07:33,300 --> 00:07:35,066
我们可以做得更好

340
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:38,633
通过使用更优化的燃料布局

341
00:07:39,266 --> 00:07:40,900
在此配置中

342
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:44,933
每根燃料棒附近正好有三根燃料棒和一个冷却单元

343
00:07:44,933 --> 00:07:47,866
这样燃料的使用率最高

344
00:07:48,333 --> 00:07:52,633
每个冷却单元只有一个燃料棒要冷却

345
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:55,500
使其持续尽可能长的时间

346
00:07:55,733 --> 00:07:59,700
这也会导致冷却单元受到完全相同的损伤

347
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:04,933
就可以很容易地将达到临界损坏的冷却单元过滤出反应堆

348
00:08:05,466 --> 00:08:06,233
终于

349
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:09,233
我们可以用足够的热容量板填充反应堆

350
00:08:09,233 --> 00:08:12,400
使它能够承受一个冷却单元的损失

351
00:08:13,266 --> 00:08:17,700
这意味着我们可以在反应堆运行时更换冷却单元

352
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,500
为了更轻松点

353
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:24,200
我们必须确保所有冷却单元处于不同的损伤水平

354
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:28,266
这样每个反应堆刻只有一个单元要更换或过热损毁

355
00:08:28,866 --> 00:08:29,700
就在那时

356
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:33,500
我不确定没有遵循 Error 的建议是否是个错误

357
00:08:34,266 --> 00:08:34,733
不管怎样

358
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:37,733
这个装置能产足够的电了

359
00:08:39,433 --> 00:08:40,800
最后

360
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:43,100
我们增加一个条件来启动反应堆

361
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:46,500
当电池电量低于四分之一

362
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:49,733
这产生了相当多的启停

363
00:08:50,466 --> 00:08:54,466
但这样的设置不需要锁存器

364
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:56,133
不管怎样

365
00:08:56,133 --> 00:09:00,900
我想我们至少解决了一集的电力问题

366
00:09:01,033 --> 00:09:02,800
下次见

367
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:03,533
拜拜

368
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:02,733
（简介放了用GT传送带做的丐版自动化，还有原作者对它的态度）

369
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:33,500
（我跟原作者聊了，他说的 Error 这个人给的建议是指上面这个反应堆）

